name: ARRC/ Alex Rorabaugh Recreation Center
description: Come play pickleball at ARRC/ Alex Rorabaugh Recreation Center in Ukiah, CA! There are 2 indoor courts. The lines are permanent, but you'll need to bring your own net. A one-time fee is required to play. Amenities include restrooms and wheelchair accessibility.

name: Birkdale United Reformed Church
description: Come play pickleball at Birkdale United Reformed Church in Ukiah, CA! There is 1 indoor wood court. The lines are permanent, and portable nets are available. Reservations are not available. The court is private. The facility includes amenities like restrooms.

name: Fort Bragg PickleBall Courts
description: Come play pickleball at Fort Bragg PickleBall Courts in Fort Bragg, CA! There are 8 outdoor hard courts. These are dedicated courts with permanent lines and nets. The courts cannot be reserved. The courts are free.

name: Harold O. Bainbridge Park
description: Harold O. Bainbridge Park is a place to play pickleball in Fort Bragg, CA. There are 2 outdoor hard courts. The lines are permanent, but you'll need to bring your own net. Amenities include restrooms, water, and lights. The courts are free.

name: Mendocino Medley
description: Come play pickleball at Mendocino Medley in Noyo, CA! There is 1 outdoor hard court. The lines are permanent, and portable nets are available. The court is private.

name: Oak Manor Park
description: Come play pickleball at Oak Manor Park in Ukiah, CA! There are 3 outdoor courts. The lines are overlaid on a tennis court, so the net is a little taller than a normal pickleball net. The courts are free.
